---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title={"A Minimal Browser UI That Stays Out of Your Way | Blanc"}
  description={"Blanc replaces a traditional tab strip and toolbar with one floating Island for tabs, navigation, blocking status, and page actions."}
  path="/features/island"
  page="feature-island"
  current="features"
  ogDescription={"One floating Island for tabs, navigation, blocking status, and page actions."}
  ogImage="/feature-island.png"
  ogImageAlt={"Blanc's floating Island over a GitHub page, showing tabs, the current site, and the blocking count."}
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline slot="head">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
  "itemListElement": [
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://blancbrowser.com/" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Features", "item": "https://blancbrowser.com/features" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "The Blanc Island", "item": "https://blancbrowser.com/features/island" }
  ]
}
</script>

<main class="feature-page feature-detail-page">
  <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb"><a href="/">home</a><span aria-hidden="true">/</span><a href="/features">features</a><span aria-hidden="true">/</span><span aria-current="page">the Island</span></nav>
  <section class="feature-hero feature-hero--detail" aria-labelledby="island-title">
    <p class="section-kicker">the blanc island</p>
    <h1 id="island-title">One small Island. The whole browser.</h1>
    <p>Tabs, navigation, the current site, and page controls live together—so the page stays in front.</p>
  </section>
  <figure class="product-capture feature-capture">
    <div class="demo-stage island-figure" data-page-tone="github" role="img" aria-label="Blanc's floating Island resting over the GitHub website, showing tab dots, back and forward navigation, and the current domain github.com.">
      <div class="demo-page" aria-hidden="true"><div class="bar w1"></div><div class="bar w2"></div><div class="bar w3"></div><div class="bar w4"></div></div>
      <picture>
        <source media="(max-width: 560px)" srcset="/shots/mobile/github.jpg">
        <img class="demo-shot show" src="/shots/desktop/github.jpg" loading="lazy" alt="" aria-hidden="true">
      </picture>
      <div class="demo-island" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="pill">
          <div class="pnav">
            <span class="pbtn"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16"><path d="M9.75 3.5 5.25 8l4.5 4.5"/></svg></span>
            <span class="pbtn off"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16"><path d="M6.25 3.5 10.75 8l-4.5 4.5"/></svg></span>
          </div>
          <div class="dots"><span></span><span class="cur"></span><span></span><span></span></div>
          <span class="pill-fav" style="background-image:url('https://icons.duckduckgo.com/ip3/github.com.ico')"></span>
          <span class="domain">github.com</span>
          <span class="psep"></span>
          <div class="pacts">
            <span class="pbtn"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16"><path d="M12.42 10.35a5 5 0 1 1-4.42-7.35c1.4 0 2.74.56 3.74 1.53L13 5.78"/><path d="M13 3v2.78h-2.78"/></svg></span>
            <span class="pbtn heart"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16"><path d="M8 13.25C4.6 11 2.75 8.9 2.75 6.6a2.85 2.85 0 0 1 5.25-1.54A2.85 2.85 0 0 1 13.25 6.6c0 2.3-1.85 4.4-5.25 6.65z"/></svg></span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <figcaption>The Island floats above the web page instead of reserving a permanent toolbar.</figcaption>
  </figure>
  <section class="feature-copy-grid" aria-labelledby="room-title">
    <div><p class="section-kicker">the page gets the room</p><h2 id="room-title">The controls are close, not constantly present.</h2></div>
    <div class="feature-copy-list">
      <article><h3>Keep the web in front.</h3><p>Blanc does not pin a traditional tab strip and toolbar above every page. The Island leaves the web with more of its own room.</p></article>
      <article><h3>See the essentials at a glance.</h3><p>At rest, the Island shows your active tab group, the current domain, and the page's blocking count in one compact surface.</p></article>
      <article><h3>Open your whole session in one place.</h3><p>Open the Island to switch tabs, navigate, favorite a page, start a private tab, or use the browser's commands—without moving the page underneath.</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="feature-close" aria-labelledby="island-close-title"><p class="section-kicker">see less browser</p><h2 id="island-close-title">Leave the chrome behind. Keep the controls.</h2><a class="cta" href="/download" data-track="feature_cta_click" data-feature="island" data-cta-position="feature-close">download blanc</a></section>
</main>
</BaseLayout>
